        <p class="mb-5 text-justify"><span class="pr-16"></span>The iBroccoGreens System is designed to enhance innovation and sustainability in agriculture. The iBroccoGreens Team took inspiration from the growing challenges faced by local farmers in maintaining consistent and efficient microgreen production, particularly in vertical soilless farming. Observing how traditional methods often led to uneven growth, excessive water use, and manual labor inefficiencies, the team envisioned a smart farming solution that integrates IoT technology with automation. We wanted to create a solution that not only benefits farmers but also promotes awareness of smart farming technologies among students and local communities. The team focused on exploring how sensors, automation, and a web-based system that would work together to monitor and control plant growth conditions. We studied various environmental factors such as humidity, temperature, and misting intervals to identify the ideal setup for Calabrese broccoli microgreens. After some trials and adjustments, the iBroccoGreens prototype is capable of automating misting schedules and monitoring vital parameters. The prototype was later integrated with a web system that allowed users to remotely monitor data and manage the growing cycles.</p>
